.cm 'Page Mode Window Commands' 'Updated on 02/25/86 by AHJ'
There are several "window" commands which allow you to change the format of the
screen display.  To execute a window command press ESC then type "W" then
another letter.  The last letter indicates the type of window operation to be
performed.  A summary of the window commands follow.

ESC W S = Split Window  ESC W L = Scroll text left    ESC W T = Set a tab stop
.*<--->                 <----->                       <----->
.* field bold
.* field bold
.* field bold
ESC W J = Join Window   ESC W R = Scroll text right   ESC W > = Set right margin
.*<--->                 <----->                       <----->
.* field bold
.* field bold
.* field bold
ESC W C = Column line   ESC W + = Turn wordwrap on    ESC W < = Set left margin
.*<--->                 <----->                       <----->
.* field bold
.* field bold
.* field bold
ESC W U = Num/Unnum     ESC W - = Turn wordwrap off   ESC W / = Auto left margin
.*<--->                 <----->                       <----->
.* field bold
.* field bold
.* field bold
ESC W N = Next window (switches to next active file)
ESC W P = Previous window (switches to previous active file)
ESC W W = Window width (switches terminal to/from "wide" mode)
.*<--->
.* field bold
.cs 2 off
.cs 3 off
